div.ab:
A SILENT Figure walks the skies
All day;
He has a solemn look and wise,
They say.
A silent Figure walks the skies
All night;
He has a sorrow in His eyes,
They write.
A silent Figure walks the skies
In pain;
He has a solemn look and wise;
He has a sorrow in His eyes;
He suffers, and He dies, He dies—
Again.
